article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 79, Pacific 67
article.story: ANAHEIM, Calif. -- Orlando Johnson scored 32 points to lead fifth-seeded UC Santa Barbara to a 79-67 victory over fourth-seeded Pacific in the quarterfinals of the Big West tournament Thursday. James Nunnally added 19 points for the Gauchos (16-13), who avenged a regular-season sweep by the fourth-seeded Tigers (16-15). Allen Huddleston led Pacific with 21 points. The defending tournament champion Gauchos (16-13) advanced to Friday's semifinals for the fourth consecutive year. Johnson scored 22 points in the second half. He gave UC Santa Barbara its biggest lead at 71-49 with a steal and a dunk. Pacific entered the game ranked second in the Big West in scoring defense but allowed UC Santa Barbara to shoot 57.1 percent. The Tigers pulled within 45-36 on a layup by Terrell Smith with 14:20 left in the second half to cap a 9-2 run but couldn't rally further.
